✨Finn Hall✨
 Houston Food Hall

Did you know that you can get amazing Texas Craft Barbecue in Downtown Houston? The Smoke is one of the vendors at Finn Hall in downtown Houston’s historic district, and you can get barbecue platters, single meat dishes and more. 

The Food Hall itself offers tons of options for different palates, so it’s a super fun spot for a mini food tour or progressive.

We started ours at Carol kay’s cafe, a brunch concept which is Southern and homey and delicious. I loved loved loved the hot honey pork belly biscuit, but bacon wrapped grilled cheese (served with tomato bisque) is also great, and smothered chicken and biscuits are hard to beat. 

At Artistry, Houston natives Andrew and Christine are serving up european style fare, like brie and berry panini, grilled chicken and goat cheese salad, and a must-not miss talian butterscotch budino.

Craft Burger is a great stop for burger and chicken lovers. It’s Chopped Champion Shannen Tune burger joint and everything is well crafted quality. We had the Juicy Lucy burger, the fried chicken, and a crazy good buffalo crispy chicken sandwich. The milkshakes are great, too.

Finn Hall is also home to a Juice Bar, Fire Noodz, Papalo for Mexican fare, and Maui Bowls for poke and Hawaiian plate lunch, and an award winning coffee bar— Three Keys Coffee was awarded the title of best roaster in all of Texas by Food & Wine Magazine. There’s also a cocktail and wine bar, where you can pull up a chair for custom crafted cocktail, wine, beer on draft and more! Don’t miss their pop-up bar-lounge this holiday season. It’s a holiday themed pop-up bar called the Cursed Cauldron and it’s open 3pm until close every day except Sundays.
📍Finn Hall @finnhallhou 
712 Main St, Houston, TX 77002

